h3. Summary
A request to https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/username

returns a list of repos where the links contain ! after the host

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Run the following API call

{code}
curl -sL -X GET -u username:password https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/username

{code}

h3. Expected Results
The links for the repos should be like:

{code}
https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/username/repo-slug/watchers
{code}

h3. Actual Results
The links for the repos are as follows:

{code}
https://bitbucket.org/!api/2.0/repositories/username/repo-slug/watchers
{code}

h3. Workaround
Use https://api.bitbucket.org for the API call instead of https://bitbucket.org/api/2

I followed the “unwatch” link in an email which has the form of {{https://bitbucket.org/api/1.0/repositories/site/master/issue/15935/unwatch/marcusriemer/--long-id--/}} and received only the following response:

{code}
{
    "type":"error",
    "error":{
        "message":"Resource removed",
        "detail":"This API is no longer supported.\n\nFor information about its removal, please refer to the deprecation notice at: <https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/deprecation-notice-v1-apis/">
    }
}
{code}
